#X text 0 60 Each grain plays a snippet of the samplerepeatedly \,
this part being grain-sizemilliseconds long.;
#X text 0 110 So we need to play the snippet1000 / grain-size times
per second.;
#X obj 270 360 *;
#X obj 270 410 /;
#X text 0 310 The values of the phasor are transformedso that they
cover the right intervalof the sample.;
#X obj 270 290 * 0.001;
#X text 0 360 Work out what grain-size is as aproportion of the length
of the sample \, e.g. 0.2 is one fifth of the sample.Multiply the
phasor by this proportionso the interval is now e.g. [0 \, 0.2].;
#X text 0 660 Multiply by the number of samples inthe sample.;
